2026-06-10 00:18:25,563 DEBUG Tool call: submit_final_result({'final_result': '## Starshield: Glossary Definition, Reporting Segment, and Revenue Disclosure\n\n### Glossary Definition\n\nThe S-1 glossary defines **"Starshield"** as:\n\n> "a secure satellite network designed specifically for government customers and national security applications."\n\n---\n\n### Reporting Segment\n\nStarshield revenue is included in the **Connectivity** segment. Specifically, it falls within the **"Enterprise & Government"** revenue line within Connectivity, alongside Starlink Mobile service offerings.\n\nThe business overview section confirms this classification:\n\n> "We generate government revenue via long term contracts for Starshield, a secure satellite network designed specifically for government customers and national security applications."\n\nAnd the segment footnote states:\n\n> "(1) Enterprise & Government revenue includes revenue from Starlink Mobile service offerings."\n\n---\n\n### Revenue Contribution Disclosure\n\n**No separate quantitative revenue contribution is disclosed for Starshield.** The filing does not break out Starshield as a discrete revenue line item, nor does it provide a percentage contribution, dollar amount, backlog figure, or any other quantitative metric specific to Starshield.\n\nThe Connectivity segment\'s revenue is disaggregated into only two categories:\n\n| Category | FY2025 | FY2024 | FY2023 |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Consumer | $7,208M | $4,830M | $2,817M |\n| Enterprise & Government | $4,179M | $2,769M | $1,052M |\n\nStarshield revenue is fully subsumed within the **Enterprise & Government** line, with no further granularity provided.\n\nThe sole quantitative composition disclosure for the Connectivity segment is:\n\n> "In 2025, revenue from consumer subscribers represented over 60% of Connectivity segment revenue."\n\nThis implies Enterprise & Government (which includes Starshield) represented less than 40% of Connectivity revenue in 2025, but no further breakdown isolating Starshield is available.\n\n---\n\n### Additional Context\n\nThe filing does describe Starshield\'s characteristics qualitatively:\n\n- **Contract type:** Multi-year, fixed-price contracts recognized over time using the **cost-to-cost input method**.\n- **Revenue recognition:** Revenue is recognized when performance creates an asset with no alternative use and the Company has an enforceable right to payment. Progress is measured via costs incurred relative to total estimated cost at completion.\n- **Risk disclosure:** Starshield contracts are described as "complex" and require significant management judgment in estimating total costs and measuring progress toward completion.\n\n**Conclusion:** While the Connectivity segment inclusion and the nature of Starshield are clearly disclosed, the S-1 provides **no separate quantitative revenue contribution disclosure** for Starshield. Investors cannot determine from the filing what portion of Connectivity or total company revenue is attributable to Starshield specifically.'})
